
LocalStorage
============

LocalStorage is a Web API provided by modern browsers that allows web applications to store key-value paris locally on the user's computer.

And you can retrieve them even after the browsers has been closed and reopended.

LocalStorage Method
-------------------

setItem(key, value)
-> stores a key-value paris

getItem(key)
-> retrieves the value associated with a key in LocalStorage

removeItem(key) 
-> removes the key-value pair associated with a key

clear()
-> removes all key-value pairs from LocalStorage.

LocalStorage Properties
-----------------------
.length
  -> returns the number of key-value pairs stored in LocalStorage.

example -> localStorage.key(0) returns the name of the first key, 
           localStorage.key(1) returns the names of the second key, and so on
           
